g.text: Recognition and tagging of persons, organization, and locations
Downloading of latest NY Times rss feed and transformation into document cells
The workflow starts with a URL to a NY Times rss news feed.
The news feed is downloaded and parsed and transformed in
Names of persons, organizations and locations are then
recognized and the corresponding tags are assigned, in order to
apply a coloring based on a tag type later on.
After transformation into a bag of words, and filtering of all non-
persons, -organizations, or –locations colors are assigned and
the terms are visualized via a Tag Cloud.
